Name: Account Manager LOG *** PER TROY
Notes:
See Account Manager Tab & Email from Troy
Subject:Account manager LOG - Invitation to edit

Team, 

Please see the first line I have for Mark here. 

Then, go down to your tab, and complete the sheet consistently as I have Mark set up. Color code and try to use the same tones for Green - Yellow and Red as the others.

Due - by end of Tuesday. 

I would like you to complete this every Friday as the last task you do before calling it a week. 

Goal of this is to put a scaleable process in place of instincts I used to grow the company. 

1- Are they happy?

Green - we are solid and see no issues 

Yellow - They are hard to feel out or within the first 90 days - Or generally not selling more cars - or have expressed dissatisfaction in anything we do. 

Red - They have put us on notice - You can tell they are just not happy - we are trending very poorly with sales - You feel any reason we could get, or expect to be fired. 

2 - What if anything is an issue - and fix it 
3. Stay relevant and HOT FRESH NEW - so they never feel unimportant - or we have gotten stale.
4. Communicate and build solid relationships. 

Thanks, 

This is important for me to be able to keep an eye on the company as I have less and less contact and input with clients on a daily basis. 

My expectation is at the end of almost every week you have have had phone conversation with - or Seen all of your clients depending on their location and what is expected. I do not count E-mails as communication in this format. 

Thank you, 

Troy

Name: Account Manager LOG - Weekly Review
Notes:
See Account Manager Tab & Email from Troy
Subject:Account manager LOG - Invitation to edit

Team, 

Please see the first line I have for Mark here. 

Then, go down to your tab, and complete the sheet consistently as I have Mark set up. Color code and try to use the same tones for Green - Yellow and Red as the others.

Due - by end of Tuesday. 

I would like you to complete this every Friday as the last task you do before calling it a week. 

Goal of this is to put a scaleable process in place of instincts I used to grow the company. 

1- Are they happy?

Green - we are solid and see no issues 

Yellow - They are hard to feel out or within the first 90 days - Or generally not selling more cars - or have expressed dissatisfaction in anything we do. 

Red - They have put us on notice - You can tell they are just not happy - we are trending very poorly with sales - You feel any reason we could get, or expect to be fired. 

2 - What if anything is an issue - and fix it 
3. Stay relevant and HOT FRESH NEW - so they never feel unimportant - or we have gotten stale.
4. Communicate and build solid relationships. 

Thanks, 

This is important for me to be able to keep an eye on the company as I have less and less contact and input with clients on a daily basis. 

My expectation is at the end of almost every week you have have had phone conversation with - or Seen all of your clients depending on their location and what is expected. I do not count E-mails as communication in this format. 

Thank you, 

Troy
